  "text": "In addition to changes in their activity, the expression of several of these factors is directly affected. Here we observed the down-regulation of ROX1 and MOT3, whose expression is regulated by Hap1 and heme [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , and up-regulation of UPC2, whose expression is repressed by Rox1 (51). Interestingly, HAP1, which serves an essential function under anaerobiosis (13), was chronically up-regulated in both media.",
